Numerous works of art were gathered together in this precinct, many
of which have been recovered, among them  the statues of the Tiber
(Louvre), the Nile (Vatican), the Ocean (Naples), and the lions (BC 1890,
321-324; Mitt. 1891, 25) in the Vatican.  For statues, columns decorated
with reliefs, etc., found here, see Cap. 357-360; RAP ii. 107-116, 27 ;
M6l. 1920, 279. Besides the literature already cited, see HJ 567-571;
